---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Ogun SDI & LULC Mapping"
  year="2024–2025"
  section="GIS Project Management"
  category="GIS Project Manager · Sivan Design"
  tools={['GeoNode', 'GeoServer', 'PostGIS', 'QGIS', 'LULC Classification', 'System Integration', 'Capacity Building']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Ogun State needed a centralized, modern geospatial platform — and a statewide Land Use/Land
        Cover (LULC) mapping deliverable built on top of it — while leaving behind a system its own
        team could run, extend and trust. Delivered by Sivan Design under the <strong>Ogun State
        Economic Transformation Project (OGSTEP)</strong> for the Ogun State Government, Nigeria, I
        served as <strong>GIS Project Manager</strong> covering the technical design, leading the
        development team, and designing and delivering the training that handed the platform to the
        Ogun SDI team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Directed the design and deployment of an open-source SDI on <strong>GeoNode</strong>, <strong>GeoServer</strong> and <strong>PostGIS</strong>, hosted on the state's own data-center VMs with <strong>OGC-compliant web services (WMS/WFS/WCS)</strong>.</li>
      <li>Directed design of the <strong>Geom Tool</strong> — a custom in-house application that lets surveyors upload structured survey data and semi-automatically generate cadastral parcel geometry for review and approval — replacing a slow manual digitization step with an auditable workflow.</li>
      <li>Led design of the cadastral layers and a statewide <strong>Unique Parcel Identifier (UPI)</strong> framework, plus a bi-directional integration between the SDI and <strong>OLARMS</strong> (the state's land-administration system) keeping spatial and administrative records in sync.</li>
      <li>Directed the statewide <strong>LULC classification</strong>, combining <strong>Sentinel-2</strong> and high-resolution satellite imagery with field-collected ground control points and a temporal change analysis.</li>
      <li>Designed and delivered hands-on training — GIS/QGIS basics, block-drawing, the Charting New Workflow course, and Administrator Training that handed over clear ongoing roles to the four-person Ogun SDI team.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        The SDI and LULC platform are live and in active use by the Ogun State Government and the
        public, with the Geom Tool and OLARMS integration now embedded in the Bureau of Lands and
        Survey's daily charting workflow — and a trained, four-person Ogun SDI team running the
        system independently.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Screenshots</h2>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-web-map.jpg`}
      alt="Ogun SDI web-map portal showing the state's Local Government Areas highlighted in green with labels and a search bar"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The Ogun SDI web-map portal — a GeoNode-based geoportal giving the state government and the public a browsable view of Ogun's spatial data, including its Local Government Areas.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-imagery.jpg`}
      alt="High-resolution aerial imagery of an Ogun State settlement showing buildings, roads and farmland used as the basis for LULC classification"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      High-resolution imagery covering the state — the raw input layered with Sentinel-2 data and ground control points to produce the statewide LULC classification.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/ogun-sdi-training.jpg`}
      alt="Administrator training session in progress, with the Ogun SDI team and Sivan Design staff working at laptops around a conference table"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The Administrator Training session — handing the platform over to the Ogun SDI team, role by role.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Project Link</h2>
    <p class="proj-body">
      The Ogun SDI geoportal is live and publicly accessible.
    </p>
    <a class="proj-external proj-external-primary" href="https://gis.ogunstate.gov.ng/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Open Ogun SDI →
    </a>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .proj-external {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3D5E35;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .proj-external:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .proj-external-primary {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: #F0EAE0;
    background: #3D5E35;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .proj-external-primary:hover { background: #2E4828; text-decoration: none; }
</style>
